[00:28] <thowe> Kaiepi, any tips on getting running on OpenBSD 6.3?

[00:33] <Kaiepi> you'll need to build dyncall and install it manually

[00:34] <Kaiepi> install libuv from ports (not pkg, that version's too old)

[00:34] <Kaiepi> then you can build rakudo with --moar-option=--has-dyncall --moar-option=--has-libuv --moar-option=--cc=clang

[00:34] <thowe> if the pkg is too old is the port in the 6.3 branch?

[00:34] <Kaiepi> yeah

[00:35] <Kaiepi> also wherever you're running perl6, the partition its mounted on needs to have wxallowed set in /etc/fstab

