[23:04] <ToddAndMargo> Hi All,  I am trying to check if a directory exists.   This works:$ p6 'say "zef.git".IO.d.Bool;'   True 

[23:04] <ToddAndMargo> But this throws an error: `if not {$WorkingDir}.IO.d.Bool  { mkdir "{$WorkingDir}", 0o766; }`     No such method 'IO' for invocant of type 'Block'

[23:05] <ToddAndMargo> What am I doing wrong, this time?

[23:05] <raschipi> It's what's on the tin, calling IO in a block doesn't work, you need to call it in a string.

